y Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Grenville","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Irish (of Norman origin): habitational name from Grainville-la-Teinturière in Seine-Maritime, France."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Theobald","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>þeud</i> ‘people, race’ + <i>bald</i> ‘bold, brave’. The first element was altered under the influence of Greek <i>theos</i> ‘god’. This name was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705192,"age":10,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":19,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Theobald de Grenville I was born about 1318, in Kilkhampton, Cornwall, England, his father, Henry Grenville Sir Lord Kilkhampton, was 25 and his mother, Anna De Wartham, was 22. He married Lady Joyce de Beaumont about 1366, in Cornwall, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1377, in his hometown, at the age of 60, and was buried in Kilkhampton, Cornwall, England."},"et":{"about 1318–1377":"umbes 1318–1377","1318–1377":"1318–1377","1318–1367":"1318–1367","1367–1381":"1367–1381","1294–1330":"1294–1330","1297–1326":"1297–1326","1330":"1330","1297":"1297","1294":"1294","1381":"1381","1326":"1326","1337":"1337","about 1318":"umbes 1318","1367":"1367","1377":"1377","1453":"1453","about 1315":"umbes 1315","about 1366":"umbes 1366","1318":"1318","1328":"1328","Kilkhampton, Cornwall, England":"Kilkhampton, Cornwall, England","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England"},"fi":{"about 1318–1377":"noin 1318–1377","1318–1377":"1318–1377","1318–1367":"1318–1367","1367–1381":"1367–1381","1294–1330":"1294–1330","1297–1326":"1297–1326","1330":"1330","1297":"1297","1294":"1294","1381":"1381","1326":"1326","1337":"1337","about 1318":"noin 1318","1367":"1367","1377":"1377","1453":"1453","about 1315":"noin 1315","about 1366":"noin 1366","1318":"1318","1328":"1328","Kilkhampton, Cornwall, England":"Kilkhampton, Cornwall, England","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England"},"fr":{"about 1318–1377":"environ 1318–1377","1318–1377":"1318–1377","1318–1367":"1318–1367","1367–1381":"1367–1381","1294–1330":"1294–1330","1297–1326":"1297–1326","1330":"1330","1297":"1297","1294":"1294","1381":"1381","1326":"1326","1337":"1337","about 1318":"environ 1318","1367":"1367","1377":"1377","1453":"1453","about 1315":"environ 1315","about 1366":"environ 1366","1318":"1318","1328":"1328","Kilkhampton, Cornwall, England":"Kilkhampton, Cornouailles, Angleterre","Cornwall, England":"Cornouailles, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Sir Theobald de Grenville I est né environ 1318, à Kilkhampton, Cornouailles, Angleterre,